    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Chalices used in some Christian rites for ablution or rinsing; the ablution chalice holds unconsecrated wine or water, which is used after the eucharistic ceremony to rinse away the remains of the consecrated host.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
